      "@id": "#a74e642d-8f01-4d95-a85c-ef1421b562c3",
      "@type": [
        "LabProtocol"
      ],
      "description": "At 12 h, 24 h and 48 h post inoculation, 1 ml of culture was removed from the anaerobic chamber, centrifuged at full speed for 30 s, and resuspended in ∼10-30 μl of supernatant. Microcopy slides were prepared by placing 2 μl of the concentrated cultures onto thin 1% agarose pads that were applied directly to the surface of the slide. Phase-contrast microscopy was performed using a HC PLAN FLUOTAR 100x/1.32 PH3 oil immersion objective on a LEICA DM2500 microscope. Two fields of view for each strain and replicate were acquired and used to calculate the percentage of spores (the number of spores divided by the total number of spores, prespores, and vegetative cells; 300 cells per field of view were analyzed).",
      "labEquipment": "LEICA DM2500 microscope, HC PLAN FLUOTAR 100x/1.32 PH3 oil immersion objective",
